pos_mean_info_list.mean: 更好的，更可取的；更合意的

word_mean_info__list.difference: 不但表示强烈的喜欢，而且含依恋之情，因此多用于能激起深厚情感的人或物。
指喜爱投合自己心意、嗜好或欲望等的人或物。
指对能提供感观或智力上满足或快乐的东西表示欣赏或喜爱。
指有选择性或偏向性的喜欢。
最常用词，往往只表不太强烈的兴趣或关注，不带强烈的感情，除非另加修饰语。
非正式用词，口语体。指非常喜爱，带强烈的感情色彩。
指按照一定的规章或法律，用投票等方式进行的认真慎重的选择。
书面用词，具有庄严、正式的感情色彩。强调精选。
口语用词，多指从个人角度仔细挑选，也含任意挑选之意。
强调个人偏爱，不一定有选择的行动。
普通用词，侧重根据个人意愿和判断从众多的对象中进行选择，着重被选者的优点。
多指在几种可能性之间进行选择。

word_group.brief_definition: 宁愿做；更喜欢做；更愿意做
显然偏好于；明显偏好于

bilingual.source: Do you prefer the song or the poem?
bilingual.target: 你更喜欢歌曲还是诗歌？

bilingual.source: I prefer music that has great lyrics.
bilingual.target: 我更喜欢歌词好的音乐。

bilingual.source: I prefer milk to coffee in the morning.
bilingual.target: 相比咖啡，我早上更喜欢喝牛奶。

bilingual.source: Would you prefer to barter or pay with money?
bilingual.target: 你更喜欢以物易物还是用钱支付？

bilingual.source: I prefer groups that play quiet and slow songs.
bilingual.target: 我更喜欢演奏安静和慢歌的乐队。

bilingual.source: Today, most inventors prefer working by themselves.
bilingual.target: 今天，大多数发明家更喜欢独自工作。

bilingual.source: I prefer movies that give me something to think about.
bilingual.target: 我更喜欢能让我思考的电影。

bilingual.source: You prefer to feel safe and comfortable when you travel.
bilingual.target: 你更喜欢在旅行时感到安全和舒适。

bilingual.source: When I'm down or tired, I prefer movies that can cheer me up.
bilingual.target: 当我情绪低落或疲惫时，我更喜欢能让我振作起来的电影。

list.abstract: prefer（英[prɪˈfɜː]，美[prɪˈfɜːr]），英语单词，作动词为更喜爱；宁可；偏爱。短语搭配有prefer to do（更喜欢做）。例句为“They prefer to drink low-fat milk.（他们更喜欢喝低脂牛奶。）” prefer相关动词类近义词有promote、present等，相关不及物动词类近义词有affect、take a fancy to。

yingyinNormal.en: I prefer soiree. Sleepover is so sophomore year.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我更喜欢"社交聚会"这个名字，"通宵派对"这个词太过时了。

yingyinNormal.en: Sri Lanka? I know you prefer sencha green, but their black tea is to die for.
yingyinNormal.zh: 斯里兰卡？我知道你更喜欢煎绿茶，不过他们的红茶好得要命。

yingyinNormal.en: That's because I don't think I will be. You prefer working in the E.R.? I do.
yingyinNormal.zh: 因为我觉得不会回去了，你更喜欢在急诊室工作吗？是啊。

yingyinNormal.en: It turns out that in this condition most people would prefer the one with some vinegar.
yingyinNormal.zh: 结果证明在这种情况下，大多数人更喜欢加了醋的啤酒。

yingyinNormal.en: I don't care for novelty editions of Monopoly. I prefer the classics: regular and Klingon.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我可不喜欢大富翁的新版本，我更喜欢经典的，普通版的和克林贡版的。

yingyinNormal.en: If you have any questions, here's the FAQ sheet, or if you prefer the human touch, I do a live web chat called Apartment Talk on Tuesday nights.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如有任何问题，这里列出了常见问题的答案，若你更喜欢人性化解答，每周四晚我提供公寓问题的在线聊天服务。

yingyinNormal.en: They prefer it if I don't barter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 公司是觉得最好不要。

yingyinNormal.en: I'd really prefer a mountain bike.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我比较喜欢登山车。

yingyinNormal.en: Of course, if that's what you prefer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 可以啊，如果你想这样。

yingyinNormal.en: You don't prefer your madam? You were listening. Maybe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不愿意称呼我为女士么？你那时在偷听？也许吧。

yingyinNormal.en: Prefer a more passive route? How about simply watching TV?
yingyinNormal.zh: 想要比较被动的方法？不如就看个电视？

yingyinNormal.en: That will do him a lot of harm. Well, what would you prefer?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那对他会很不利。那你想我怎么样？

yingyinNormal.en: Or if you prefer, this table is available. That might be fun.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这一桌也是空的。一起坐应该不错。

yingyinNormal.en: That is so sweet! But I prefer the gold collection, but thank you.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真好，但我更想要金饰，还是要谢谢你。

yingyinNormal.en: You read a lot? I prefer being read to. That's over now, isn't it?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你读了很多书吧？我还是喜欢听人念。可那已经结束了，不是吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Of course. I can help you. Or if you prefer, I could step outside.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当然，我可以帮你，你不愿意的话，我可以在外面。

yingyinNormal.en: Well, I would prefer if people told me exactly what is on their mind.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我宁愿大家直接告诉我他们心中真实的想法。

yingyinNormal.en: Ah, yes. Such clinical language. I would prefer the more narrative voice.
yingyinNormal.zh: 对，如此医学临床的用语，我还是喜欢旁白口吻。

yingyinNormal.en: But, of course, we'd prefer if you stay on. Hope that goes without saying.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但当然，我们更希望你留下。希望这是不言自明的。

yingyinNormal.en: If you requested to transfer, we can make that happen. If that's what you'd prefer.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果你想转部门，我们可以做到。如果你想要我转走的话。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

examination_example.sentence: Only strong people <highlight>prefer</highlight> to smile and value their life instead of crying and complaining about something.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 只有坚强的人才更喜欢微笑并珍惜自己的生活，而不是哭泣和抱怨。

examination_example.sentence: Generally however British land artists <highlight>preferred</highlight> to get away from towns, gravitating towards landscapes that are traditionally considered beautiful.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但通常英国地景艺术家更喜欢远离城镇，而被吸引到那些传统意义上的美景。

examination_example.sentence: They <highlight>prefer</highlight> to come and go as opportunity calls them.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们更喜欢跟随机会的号召或来或走。

sense_info_list.en: submit (a charge or a piece of information) for consideration

examination_example.sentence: One of the most effective ways to change attitude is to start behaving as if you already think the way you'd <highlight>prefer</highlight> to.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 改变态度最有效的方法之一就是开始表现得好像你已经按照自己喜欢的方式去思考。

examination_example.sentence: Similarly, people rated cars, clocks, and watches with wide faces as more dominant-looking than narrow-faced ones, and <highlight>preferred</highlight> them — especially in competitive situations.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 同样，人们认为宽的汽车、钟表和手表比窄的更能体现出一个人的统治力，并且偏爱它们-尤其是在竞争激烈的情况下。

examination_example.sentence: Indifference is also the <highlight>preferred</highlight> option among those who are socially lazy.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 对于那些有“社交懒惰症”的人来说，保持冷漠也是不二的选择。

examination_example.sentence: Decision fatigue assuredly leads to inaction and the possible chagrin (懊恼) of a decision maker who might otherwise prefer a new <highlight>course</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 决策疲劳肯定会导致无所作为，还可能会使决策者感到懊恼，否则他们可能更喜欢新的方法。

examination_example.sentence: I'd much <highlight>prefer</highlight> to have my data used by the maximum number of people to ask their own questions.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我非常希望有尽可能多的人使用我的数据来提出自己的问题。

direction_info.description:

word_usage.usage: prefer doing to doing表示两种活动中更喜欢哪一种：He prefers doing to saying. 他更喜欢做而不是说。
prefer doing表示一般情况下“更喜欢某种活动”，而prefer to do表示在一个特定场合下“更喜欢”。
prefer sb. (not) to do sth. 表示“宁愿/更喜欢某人（不）做某事 “：I prefer you not to come back. 我宁愿你不回来。
prefer sth. to sth. 表示两者相比之下更喜欢哪一个：prefer coffee to tea 比起茶更爱咖啡
prefer to do...rather than do...表示“与其…不如…，宁愿…而不愿…”：I prefer to stay at home watching TV rather than go dancing. 我宁愿待在家里看电视也不愿去跳舞。

word_usage.usage: prefer doing表示一般情况下“更喜欢某种活动”，而prefer to do表示在一个特定场合下“更喜欢”。
prefer doing to doing表示两种活动中更喜欢哪一种：He prefers doing to saying. 他更喜欢做而不是说。
prefer sth. to sth. 表示两者相比之下更喜欢哪一个：prefer coffee to tea 比起茶更爱咖啡
prefer to do...rather than do...表示“与其…不如…，宁愿…而不愿…”：I prefer to stay at home watching TV rather than go dancing. 我宁愿待在家里看电视也不愿去跳舞。
prefer sb. (not) to do sth. 表示“宁愿/更喜欢某人（不）做某事 “：I prefer you not to come back. 我宁愿你不回来。

word_usage.usage:
prefer相当于like... better。
如：I prefer cartoons.= I like cartoons better.
我更喜欢卡通片。

prefer A to B，比起B,更喜欢A 
I much prefer jazz to rock music.
我喜欢爵士乐远胜于摇滚乐。

I prefer to wear clothes made of natural fibers.
我更喜欢穿由天然纤维制成的衣服。

prefer to do A rather than do B，宁愿做A事，也不愿做B事
I prefer to go to the zoo rather than slay at home.
我宁愿去动物园，也不愿待在家里。
